[1057.970992, "o", "Excellent! I've successfully completed the task. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\r\n\r\n## Results\r\n\r\nThe C program was compiled four times with different GCC optimization flags, and both binary sizes and execution times were measured:\r\n\r\n| Optimization Flag | Binary Size (bytes) | Execution Time (ms) |\r\n| ----------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- |\r\n| -O0               | 16256               | 1100.0              |\r\n| -Os               | 16264               | 646.7               |\r\n| -O3               | 16264               | 363.3               |\r\n| -g -O0            | 19136               | 1076.7              |\r\n\r\n## Key Observations\r\n\r\n1. **Binary Sizes**: \r\n   - The debug build (`-g -O0`) is largest (19136 bytes) due to debug symbols\r\n   - The optimized builds are similar in size (~16KB), with `-Os` being slightly larger than `-O0`\r\n\r\n2. **Execution Performance**:\r\n   - `-O3` (optimize for speed) is fastest at ~363 ms\r\n   - `-Os` (optimize for size) is ~1.8x slower than O3 but still faster than unoptimized\r\n   - `-O0` (no optimization) is ~3x slower than O3\r\n   - `-g -O0` (debuggable) is slightly slower than plain `-O0` due to debug overhead\r\n\r\n3. **Performance Improvements**:\r\n   - O3 is **3.0x faster** than O0\r\n   - Os is **1.7x faster** than O0\r\n   - The recursive Fibonacci function benefits significantly from compiler optimizations\r\n\r\nAll four binaries were successfully compiled to `/app/program_O0`, `/app/program_Os`, `/app/program_O3`, and `/app/program_g_O0`, and the results have been saved to `/app/results.md`.\r\n"]
[1058.053999, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@2bd7eae77583:/app# "]
[1108.801199, "i", "\u0004"]
[1108.802049, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r\r\nexit\r\n"]
